                      "I have an update on my Yarbo. It works, it's awesome, I love it, I'm keeping it! I can't wait
                      to start receiving future updates and added features like I do on my Teslas. I discovered
                      yesterday that we lack a 'chute clog' sensor. My snow thrower became a snow pusher. I had to go
                      out and clear the chute 1 time. My guess is that I didn't have the auger speed set high enough
                      for the area by the road where the plow piles reside. The snowblower is capable and has proven
                      its usefulness to me...and my neighbor. Yesterday, it rescued a neighbor who broke a sheer pin
                      on the impeller of his 20 year old Ariens. I made a quick map around his remaining snow and
                      pushed the go button on my phone. We talked while we observed. Yarbo needs to offer all the
                      owners some pre-IPO stock purchase rights before they decide to list on US stock exchanges. I'm
                      in on this tech. The core will not be the only robot. I look forward to the spring when I can
